<!--

This file defines army compositions in game.

Fields index:
	Index   		- it is simply composition index. Provide valid integer number.
				  See reference on indexes in original game below.

	Priority   		- it is importance of the composition to the Queen. Most important
				  compositions are getting reinforcements first, than less important. 
				  Nobody will get reinforcements, if Queen have no free troops.

	ElitePercentage		- it is a chance to be elite for every soldier in squad, i.e. when
				  game create a squad every soldier is rolled a chance to be elite.
				  Provide integer from interval [0..100].

	TroopPercentage		- it is like ElitePercentage, but for regular troops.

	AdminPercentage		- and this is something different. This value is used to calculate
				  number of admins in squad:
				      NumAdmins = AdminPercentage * StartPopulation / 100

	DesiredPopulation	- it is the number of soldiers the Queen want to have in this
				  composition. Provide integer value.

	StartPopulation		- it is the number of soldiers at the start of the new campagin.
				  Provide integer value.

Indexes reference in original JA2:

Index	Short name							Description
0		QUEEN_DEFENCE					The most important sector, the queen's palace.
1		GRYFINDER_DEFENCE			The town surrounding the queen's palace.
2		GRYFINDER_SAMSITE				A sam site near Gryfinder (higher priority)
3		LEVEL1_DEFENCE					The sectors immediately adjacent to Gryfinder (defence and spawning area)
4		LEVEL2_DEFENCE					Two sectors away from Gryfinder (spawning area)
5		ROADBLOCK1							Strategic roadblocks near Gryfinder
6		NASA_DEFENCE						The top secret military base containing lots of elites
7		ASGARD_DEFENCE					Rest point, nearest to Gryfinder
8		ASPENWOOD_DEFENCE			The most-industrial town in Arulco (more mine income)
9		ASPENWOOD_MINE
10	INITIAL_WELCOME					Assault force that greets the player & NPCs upon arrival in game
11	LIMESTONE								The barren, neglected town 
12	RWENDIA_DEFENCE				Strong rebel sentiment as the rich fortunes were seized
13	RWENDIA_SAMSITE					East sam site, important for military town air coverage
14	AZKABAN_PRISON					Prison, well defended, but no point in retaking
15	ALASPAR_DEFENCE				The military town of Arulco.  Also very important for queen.
16	ALASPAR_MINE						Mine income AND administrators
17	DRASNIA_DEFENCE				Medical town, large, eastern
18	DRASNIA_MINE
19	DURANTH_DEFENCE				The town actually run by outlaws.
20	QUEVELIN_DEFENCE				Small town, small mine, far away.
21	QUEVELIN_MINE
22	QUEVELIN_SAMSITE				South sam site.
23	LODENBURG_AIRPORT			A runway capable for small cargo plane landing
24	LODENBURG_DEFENCE			Medium town, normal, central.
25	LODENBURG_MINE
26	LODENBURG_SAMSITE			Southeast sam site (least important to queen of all sam sites)
27	ROADBLOCK2							Secondary roadblocks
28	ROADBLOCK3							Faraway roadblocks


Army composition soldier count calculation:

1)  game calculate number of admins (NumAdmins = AdminPercentage * StartPopulation / 100)
2)  for the rest soldiers game makes a loop:
2a) soldier check to be elite
2b) soldier check to be regular troop
2c) if both checks failed, none soldier is added
3)  step 2 is executed until there are unchecked soldiers left


NOTE: Maximum 60 army compositions can be used in game.

Changes require starting of a new game.

-->
